From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gnoblin Developers <gnoblin@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 00:45:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] context: ignore duplicate termination while loop is stopping

The visible Mutter Devkit path can receive more than one teardown signal:
the host viewer disappears, remote sessions close, and the process may also
receive SIGTERM from the harness cleanup. Once the main loop has been asked
to quit, an additional meta_context_terminate() call should be harmless.

Keep warning when termination is requested in the wrong context state, but
do not emit a runtime-check warning for the already-stopping main loop case.
---
 src/core/meta-context.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/core/meta-context.c b/src/core/meta-context.c
index 579e450..ea9f607 100644
--- a/src/core/meta-context.c
+++ b/src/core/meta-context.c
@@ -594,7 +594,8 @@ meta_context_terminate (MetaContext *context)
   g_return_if_fail (META_IS_CONTEXT (context));
 
   g_warn_if_fail (priv->state == META_CONTEXT_STATE_RUNNING);
-  g_warn_if_fail (g_main_loop_is_running (priv->main_loop));
+  if (!priv->main_loop || !g_main_loop_is_running (priv->main_loop))
+    return;
 
   g_main_loop_quit (priv->main_loop);
 }
